attribute.attributeDefinition:
macrophytes were identified by a six-digit species code, which can be further divided into taxons of specific levels;
digits 1-2 = family digits 3-4 = genus digits 5-6 = species
summation Lines: vegetation with a species code 000001 and 01 for live is the vegetation of "live other" species that could not be identified. vegetation with a species code 000001 and 02 for dead is the vegetation of "dead other" species that could not be identified . vegetation with a species code 000001 and 00 for live and dead col. is the total no. of vegetation of "dead other" or "live other" species that could not be identified.
